name: Community Vaccination Center at Bellingham Technical College
notes: We are currently vaccinating eligible individuals as determined by Washington State Department of Health ages 18 and older.  If appointments are full, you can click on “Waiting List” to register yourself for standby appointments for that scheduling day only.  If there are extra doses of vaccine at the end of the day, individuals on the waiting list will be called in scheduling order.  You can also make an appointment by calling 360-778-6075 Monday through Friday from 8:30 AM to 4:00 PM.  Phone appointments are available for people who do not have an email, internet access, need interpretation services, or are having difficulty navigating the site.  On-site registration is available as well. Masks must be worn at all times at the site and six-foot distancing will be maintained.  The site is ADA accessible.  For directions, visit www.vaccinatewhatcom.org.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Ash Way Park & Ride DRIVE THROUGH - COVID Vaccine Site
notes:
********THIS IS A PFIZER CLINIC***********
Everyone 16 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination.
 
Please also note that, even if you are otherwise eligible, you must be 18 or older for the Moderna or Johnson & Johnson vaccine, and 16 or older for the Pfizer vaccine (parent/guardian must be present to sign the consent form).
 
Appointments are highly recommended but not required.  Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves.
 
****IF YOU ARE SCHEDULING YOUR 2ND DOSE APPOINTMENT, YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record)****
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
